---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
// Disclaimer page per PRD Addendum section 4.3 - Critical for blog, products, tools
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Disclaimer — Projexions"
  description="Disclaimer for Projexions website content, blog posts, resources, tools, and digital products."
  currentPath="/disclaimer"
>
  <div class="page-container">
    <h1 class="serif-heading text-4xl font-semibold mb-6 text-center">Disclaimer</h1>

    <div class="prose-content">
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">General Information</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Projexions provides digital tools, templates, reference materials, written content, and consulting focused on financial organization, record readiness, and systems design.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          All content, products, and services are provided for informational and organizational purposes only.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">No Professional Advice</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Projexions does not provide accounting advice, tax advice, legal advice, or financial advice.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Nothing on this website—including blog posts, resources, tools, digital products, or consulting sessions—should be interpreted as professional advice or as a substitute for services provided by licensed professionals.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">No Filing, Representation, or Compliance Services</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">
          Projexions does not:
        </p>
        <ul class="resource-list text-lg mb-6">
          <li>Prepare or file tax returns</li>
          <li>Represent individuals or businesses before tax authorities or regulators</li>
          <li>Provide audits, attest services, or compliance opinions</li>
          <li>Interpret tax law, accounting standards, or regulatory requirements</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Users are responsible for engaging qualified professionals when advice, filing, or compliance services are required.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Tools, Resources, and Digital Products</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">
          Projexions tools, templates, checklists, spreadsheets, Notion workspaces, guides, and digital products are designed to help users:
        </p>
        <ul class="resource-list text-lg mb-6">
          <li>Organize financial information</li>
          <li>Assess record condition</li>
          <li>Identify gaps and priorities</li>
          <li>Support internal decision-making</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          They do not replace professional review, judgment, or advice tailored to a specific business or situation.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Consulting Services</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Consulting sessions offered by Projexions are limited to discussion of systems, workflows, organization, and tool usage.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">
          Consulting does not include:
        </p>
        <ul class="resource-list text-lg mb-6">
          <li>Accounting advice</li>
          <li>Tax advice</li>
          <li>Legal advice</li>
          <li>Financial or investment advice</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          No accountant-client, advisor-client, fiduciary, or professional relationship is created through consulting sessions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Blog Content and Written Materials</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Blog posts and written materials reflect experience, observation, and general patterns observed across businesses.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          They are not recommendations, instructions, or advice. Readers should not rely on blog content as a basis for decisions without consulting appropriate professionals.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Some links on this website may be affiliate links. Projexions may receive compensation if users choose to engage with third-party products or services through these links.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Affiliate relationships do not influence the structure, content, or intent of Projexions tools, products, or recommendations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">No Warranties</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          All information, tools, and products are provided "as is," without warranties of any kind, express or implied, including accuracy, completeness, or suitability for a particular purpose.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">User Responsibility</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">
          Users are solely responsible for:
        </p>
        <ul class="resource-list text-lg mb-6">
          <li>Their financial records</li>
          <li>Their business and personal decisions</li>
          <li>How tools and information are applied</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Projexions is not liable for decisions made or actions taken based on use of this website, its content, or its products.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
